title: Syrian jets bomb rebel-held Homs district, kill several people
text: Syrian jets bomb rebel-held Homs district, kill several people Reuters | Feb 8, 2017, 07.21 PM IST (Image courtesy: Google maps) BEIRUT: Syrian government jets bombed a rebel-held district of Homs city on Wednesday killing several people, rescue workers and a monitoring group reported. The raids hit the al-Waer neighbourhood, the British-based Syrian Observatory for Human Rights and the Syrian Civil Defence , a rescue service operating in rebel-held territory, said. The Observatory put the death toll at 8 and more than two-dozen wounded. The Civil Defence did not give a figure. A military media unit run by Damascus ally Hezbollah said the army had fired rockets at militants in al-Waer, but that the insurgents had fired first.
